---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SEGMENTS, site, description, pageTitle } from '../../content';
import { SEGMENTS as SEGS } from '../../data/segments';

const path = '/for';
const title = pageTitle(site, 'for');
const desc = description(site, 'for');
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={desc} site={site} path={path}>
  <section class="py-14 md:py-20">
    <div class="container">
      <h1 class="hero-title text-5xl md:text-6xl">Shopify SMS apps by store type</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 max-w-3xl text-xl text-cyan-100">SMS behavior should change by catalog, margin, replenishment window, and consent tolerance. These twelve playbooks adapt TCPA-safe texting to real Shopify categories.</p>
      <div class="mt-10 grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
        {SEGS.map((s) => (
          <a class="card" href={`/for/${s.slug}`}>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-black text-white">{s.name}</h2>
            <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-cyan-100">Built around {s.pain}.</p>
          </a>
        ))}
      </div>
      <article class="prose-shopify card mt-12 max-w-4xl">
        <h2>How to use store-type SMS guides</h2>
        <p>Start with your category playbook before comparing logos. Fashion drops, supplement replenishment, and wholesale reorder nudges should not share the same SMS cadence or consent assumptions. Each guide ranks Postscript for SMS-native execution, Sequenzy for lifecycle email coordination, and Klaviyo or Omnisend when you want bundled channels.</p>
        <p>Every playbook includes TCPA notes, cost-per-message framing, quiet-hour guidance, and implementation checklists. Read the segment page, then open the relevant use-case guide for cart recovery, replenishment, or launch alerts.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

    <div class="prose-shopify card mt-8">
      <h2>SMS operations depth 1: two-way SMS reply inbox…</h2>
      <p>For <strong>for index</strong>, two-way SMS reply inbox ownership assigned to one operator is not optional infrastructure. Shopify SMS apps that recover urgent revenue without wrecking consent treat every text as a scarce interrupt — cart recovery after meaningful checkout intent, launch access for opted-in VIPs, replenishment when SKU usage data supports timing.</p>
      <p>Postscript remains the SMS-native benchmark on this site: TCPA tooling, two-way replies, Shopify event triggers, and broadcast controls. Sequenzy is deliberately ranked as lifecycle email layer beside SMS — welcome depth, post-purchase education, winback arcs that should not be crammed into 160 characters. Klaviyo and Omnisend fit when one team wants bundled SMS with segmentation; Attentive when enterprise acquisition economics justify custom contracts.</p>
      <p>Run the math before scaling: platform fee plus carrier fee plus average discount per recovered order. A text that needs 25% off to convert may be negative contribution margin even when attribution dashboards look green. Pair channels deliberately — email for proof and education, SMS for timing — and never duplicate the same offer within twenty-four hours unless the subscriber opted into high-frequency updates.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Document opt-in source, message type promised, and maximum weekly frequency per segment.</li>
        <li>Configure quiet hours before enabling automations; audit checkout and popup copy quarterly.</li>
        <li>Assign one owner for reply inbox, suppression maps, and pre-launch TCPA review.</li>
        <li>Measure opt-out rate by flow, cost per incremental order, and full-price repeat purchase quality.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

